'''Artificial gravity''' was a mean of generating [[gravity]] within a [[Starship|vessel]] traveling in [[Realspace|space]] such that those traveling aboard it could remain upright.<ref name="dark" />

The ''[[Moveable Feast]]'' was an example of a vessel equipped with artificial gravity. When the ship was damaged while [[Lina Graf|Lina]] and [[Milo Graf]] were traveling aboard it as [[prisoner]]s, the artificial gravity began to weaken, causing Milo to nearly float away when he stumbled after the ship itself juddered.<ref name="dark" />

When the [[Spectres]] were aboard [[Transport 651]] to [[Mission to free Wookiee prisoners|rescue]] [[Wookiee]] [[prison]]ers, [[Sabine Wren]] had the [[astromech droid]] [[C1-10P|Chopper]] shut down the ship's [[Artificial gravity generator|gravity generator]], taking down artificial gravity for two [[Standard minute|minutes]] and greatly troubling the [[Galactic Empire|Imperials]] on-board.<ref name="spark">''[[Star Wars Rebels: Spark of Rebellion]]''</ref>

The [[scientist]] [[Fyzen Gor]] was able to artificially replicate a gravitational center around his [[Phylanx Redux Transmitter]].<ref name="Last Shot">''[[Last Shot]]''</ref>

